# Error Handling and Observability
- Do not swallow async errors; either rethrow or return a structured error response (`{ ok: false, error }`) for runtime messages.
- Keep background message handlers resilient: normalize unknown errors before logging/responding.
- Use `logger` (`src/shared/logger.js`) instead of raw `console.*` so logs stay searchable and consistent.
- Log intent + context (action, module, lightweight metadata), but avoid logging full document content or sensitive data.
- Prefer explicit failure paths in bootstrap/render flows: fail fast on missing critical data and exit early on unsupported states.
